# Supabase Migration Convention

**Never create a new migration file** when the change can go into an existing one. Always edit the relevant existing migration instead.

## When to edit vs. create

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Adding a column to an existing table | Edit the migration that created that table |
| Changing a function or RPC | Edit the migration that last defined that function |
| Truly independent, irreversible schema change (e.g. new table, new extension) | Create a new file |

## How to edit safely

All DDL in this project is written to be **idempotent** (`CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS`, `ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS`, `DROP CONSTRAINT IF EXISTS` / re-add, `CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION`, etc.). Follow the same pattern when adding to an existing file so re-running the migration never fails.

## Examples

```sql
-- ✅ Adding a column — edit the table's migration
alter table public.user_details
  add column if not exists min_age_pref integer not null default 18;

-- ✅ Updating a function — replace in-place in the migration that owns it
drop function if exists public.get_user_profile;
create or replace function public.get_user_profile(...) ...

-- ❌ Don't create 20260429000000_age_preferences.sql just to add columns
--    to user_details and tweak nearby_users — edit the originals instead.
```
